      <para id="id6387210">If transition metals are present then decomposition occurs, <link target-id="eip-22222"/>, and therefore, ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid (EDTA, <link target-id="id1168442753501"/>) is added to complex the transition metal ions. The as produced hydrazine solution can be concentrated by distillation to give a 65% solution. Anhydrous hydrazine is formed by the distillation from NaOH.</para>

